===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms}}
Commonly assumed to be related to {{och-l|羌}} ({{zh-ref|Pulleyblank, 2000}}), though not necessarily ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}); {{och-l|羊|sheep}} in the graphs may be just phonetic or also semantic, signifying "names referring to nomads" ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2009}}).

{{zh-ref|Pulleyblank (2000)}} reconstructs {{och-l|姜|tr=*(C)ɰàŋ}} and proposes etymological connection to {{och-l|姬|tr= *(C)ɰə̀ɰ}}, {{zh-l|*姜}} being the "collateral, wife-supplying counterpart" to {{zh-l|姬*}} the "ruling clan", both being "two intermarrying moieties"; he also points to other word-pairs, including {{ltc-l|似|to resemble}} < *-''əɰʔ'' and {{ltc-l|像|to imitate, image}} < *''-aŋʔ'', which display the phonetic correspondences: *''-ɰ'' vs. *''-ŋ'' as well *''-ə-'' vs. *''-a-'' (ibid.).

